    • Constructor Detail

      • SequentialTuner

        public SequentialTuner(IInPUT input,
               java.util.List<IDesign> problems,
               java.lang.String studyId,
               boolean minProblem)
                throws InPUTException
        A sequential tuner requires an experimental context to be set, that extends the use of an IInPUT element to a concrete problem instance under investigation. To differentiate between different problem instances allows for a differentiated analysis of the results with respect to problem features. However, the setting of problem is optional; a problem context might not even be reasonable, desired, or available (e.g. when interested in configurations for a single possibly very special instance only). When defined, it has to match the problem feature space provided by input.
        Parameters:
        input -
        studyId -
        problem -
        Throws:
        InPUTException
